\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1. What is AliNet?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 AliNet is a GNN-based model tailored for 
\f0\b Knowledge Graph (KG) entity alignment
\f1\b0 , tackling the issue of 
\f0\b non-isomorphic neighborhoods
\f1\b0  (i.e., when equivalent entities have different immediate neighbors across KGs). It achieves this via:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls73\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Multi-hop neighborhood aggregation, including 
\f5\i distant neighbors
\f1\i0  to expand structural overlap.\
\ls73\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 A 
\f0\b gated attention mechanism
\f1\b0  to focus on helpful distant neighbors and reduce noise.\
\ls73\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 A 
\f0\b relation consistency loss
\f1\b0  to fine-tune entity embeddings.\uc0\u8232 ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/nju-websoft/AliNet?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \ul GitHub}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1911.08936?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \ul arXiv}})\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Evaluated across 5 datasets with thorough ablations, it's published in AAAI 2020 with strong citation and impact.\uc0\u8232 ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://arxiv.org/abs/1911.08936?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \ul arXiv}})\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

