\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 3. How to Avoid Duct Tape\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 The danger you called out \'97 \'93duct tape and bubblegum\'94 \'97 is real when we just drop repos in. The antidote is 
\f0\b contracts and scorecards
\f1\b0 :\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls110\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Adapter contracts
\f1\b0  (trainer, aggregator, selector, planner, embedding): all frameworks plug into these, never directly into daemons.\
\ls110\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Artifacts & ledger discipline
\f1\b0 : every run produces model_card.jsonld, onnx_check.json (if neural), eval_meta.json.\
\ls110\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Promotion gates
\f1\b0 : SHACL + ONNX cosine + eval deltas + framework-specific gates (e.g. DP epsilon for federated, monotonicity for lattice, routing entropy for sNDF).\
\ls110\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Scorecards & ADRs
\f1\b0 : one page per framework recording fit, integration cost, observability, maintenance, and a decision (adopt / trial / sandbox / reject).\
\ls110\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Observability
\f1\b0 : every adapter surfaces Prometheus metrics that can be plotted in Grafana (accuracy curves, resource use, DP epsilon, robust_agg flags, etc.).\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 That way, TritFabric sees them all as 
\f0\b capabilities
\f1\b0  rather than \'93random repos.\'94\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

