\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1) Octonion-Valued Neural Networks (OVNNs): stability, delay & finite-time control\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 What\'92s new
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls123\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 OVNNs are the highest-dimensional normed-division algebra nets (8D; non-commutative & non-associative). The paper shows you can 
\f0\b decompose any OVNN
\f1\b0  into 
\f0\b eight coupled real-valued NNs
\f1\b0 , then prove 
\f0\b \'b5-stability
\f1\b0 under 
\f0\b unbounded, asynchronous time-varying delays
\f1\b0 , and design 
\f0\b finite-time controllers
\f1\b0  (including 
\f0\b adaptive
\f1\b0 ones) that guarantee convergence in two phases (2PM) .\
\ls123\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 A 2024 follow-up generalizes to 
\f0\b time-scales
\f1\b0  (continuous, discrete, or hybrid): leakage + mixed delays, Halanay-type inequalities, and 
\f0\b controller gains via LMIs
\f1\b0  for 
\f0\b exponential stability & synchronization
\f1\b0  (also with a state-feedback K1..K4 structure) .\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Why it expands our capability
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls124\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Expressivity:
\f1\b0  8-component algebra captures cross-channel phase/energy couplings a real or complex net can\'92t.\
\ls124\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Guarantees:
\f1\b0  we can 
\f0\b train for control-theoretic targets
\f1\b0  (finite-time/exponential stability, sync) and compile them into runtime contracts.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 SR we\'92ll train
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls125\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Delay & rate laws:
\f1\b0  recover 
\f0\b \uc0\u964 (t)
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b \'b5(t)
\f1\b0  (e.g., exponential/power) from data that satisfy the \'b5-stability definitions; infer the 
\f0\b Lipschitz bounds
\f1\b0  (\uc0\u955 , \u948 ) used in the proofs.\
\ls125\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Controller synthesis:
\f1\b0  learn closed-forms for 
\f0\b U\uc0\u8467 p(t)
\f1\b0  gains in the finite-time controllers and the 
\f0\b adaptive rules
\f1\b0 \uc0\u954 \u729 (t), \u954 \u770 \u729 (t) that meet the two-phase proofs; discover 
\f0\b time-scale grain
\f1\b0  \uc0\u956 (t) and 
\f0\b Halanay coefficients
\f1\b0  to satisfy the LMI conditions on your dataset.\
\ls125\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Octonion coupling rules:
\f1\b0  recover compact algebraic couplings (effective \'93weight-sharing\'94 across the 8 real sub-nets) that respect the Cayley-Dickson structure used in the decomposition.\
