\cf0 Below is a precise, implementation-oriented 
\f0\b multi-algebra embedding
\f1\b0  for your network that behaves like a 
\f0\b Noetherian system
\f1\b0 : every layer declares the algebra it lives in, the symmetry group acting on it, the invariant form it preserves, and the 
\f0\b Noether charges
\f1\b0  it must conserve (up to numerical or learned dissipation). Cross-layer coercions (functors) let you mix (\\mathbb C,\\mathbb H,\\mathbb O) as well as Clifford/Symmetric\'96space blocks in one model without duct-tape.\
I\'92ll give you:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls158\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	0.	}the 
\f0\b formal contract
\f1\b0  per layer (algebra, group action, conserved charges),\
{\listtext	0.	}the 
\f0\b discrete Noether
\f1\b0  machinery we use during training,\
{\listtext	0.	}the 
\f0\b inter-algebra exchange
\f1\b0  (C
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1 H
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1 O and back; Clifford/Symmetric-space adapters),\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b losses/integrators
\f1\b0  that make conservation practical,\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b symbolic-regression (SR) heads
\f1\b0  that learn closed-form invariants/schedules,\
{\listtext	0.	}a 
\f0\b TritFabric config
\f1\b0  and 
