\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 0) Why \'93Noetherian\'94\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Noether\'92s theorem says: 
\f5\i every continuous symmetry of the Lagrangian yields a conserved charge
\f1\i0 . For neural systems this becomes: 
\f5\i every declared group action on hidden state yields a diagnostic quantity that should remain constant along the learned flow (unless we model explicit dissipation)
\f1\i0 . This gives you 
\f0\b stability, interpretability, and self-diagnostics
\f1\b0 .\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1) Layer contract (what every block must declare)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 For each layer (L) (conv/attention/recurrent), we register:\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 algebra:         C | H | O | Cl(p,q) | SPD(n) | Grass(k,n) | Lagrangian(n) \'85\
group:           U(1) | SU(2) | G2 | O(n) | U(n) | Sp(n) | product/semidirect\
representation:  rho: G -> Aut(V_A) (matrix blocks implementing action)\
invariant_form:  <x,y>_A (Hermitian, symplectic, quadratic, SPD metric\'85)\
connection:      A (bundle or principal connection; horizontal update rule)\
integrator:      symplectic_euler | cayley | lie_midpoint | manifold_adam\
charges:         \{J_i\}  # momentum maps / invariants to be computed\
coercions_in:    \{from: algebra, morphism: \'85\}    # see \'a73\
coercions_out:   \{to: algebra, morphism: \'85\}\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls159\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 algebra (A)
\f1\b0  chooses the typed tensor space:\uc0\u8232 (\\mathbb C) (2-real), (\\mathbb H) (4-real), (\\mathbb O) (8-real), Clifford (Cl(p,q)); or a 
\f0\b symmetric space
\f1\b0  (SPD, Grassmann, Lagrangian).\
\ls159\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 group (G)
\f1\b0  declares symmetry; 
\f0\b representation (\\rho)
\f1\b0  tells how the group acts on activations.\
\ls159\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 invariant form
\f1\b0  is preserved by that action (e.g., quaternion unit norm; symplectic form for Lagrangian layers).\
\ls159\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 connection
\f1\b0  gives horizontal lifts for Hopf-bundle typed states.\
\ls159\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 charges (\{J_i\})
\f1\b0  are the layer\'92s Noether invariants (phase, angular momentum, symplectic area, Casimirs, \'85).\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 2) Discrete Noether for learning\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 We discretize time (depth (k\\to k+1)) with a 
\f0\b variational/symplectic integrator
\f1\b0  so \'93conservation up to integrator error\'94 is automatic.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 2.1 Lagrangian/Flow\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls160\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Hidden state (,h_k \\in V_A,) (typed by the algebra).\
\ls160\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Discrete Lagrangian (L_d(h_k, h_\{k+1\}; \\theta)) (e.g., energy-like term + task loss).\
\ls160\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Update rule (,h_\{k+1\} = \\Phi(h_k, x_k; \\theta)) computed by the layer, 
\f0\b retracted
\f1\b0  to the manifold.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 2.2 Momentum map (Noether charge)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Given infinitesimal generator (\\xi \\in \\mathfrak g) (Lie algebra), the discrete momentum map:\
[\uc0\u8232 J_\\xi(h_k) ;\\approx; \\left\\langle,\\frac\{\\partial L_d\}\{\\partial \\dot h\},,,\\xi\\cdot h_k,\\right\\rangle_\{A\}\u8232 ]\
Concretely:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls161\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 (\\mathbb C)/U(1) (phase)
\f1\b0 : (J(h)=\\Im(\\bar h\\odot h')) (phase rate).\
\ls161\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 (\\mathbb H)/SU(2) (3D rotation)
\f1\b0 : (J(h)=h^*,\\sigma, h') (Pauli/quaternion form).\
\ls161\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Symplectic (Lagrangian)
\f1\b0 : (J(h)=h^\\top \\Omega, h') (area), (\\Omega) is the symplectic matrix.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 2.3 Loss terms\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 L = L_task + \uc0\u955 _cons \u8721 _i || J_i(h_\{k+1\}) - J_i(h_k) ||^2 + \u955 _inv E_g || f(x) - f(g\'b7x) ||^2 + \u955 _geo || Retr_M(W - \u951 \u8711 W) - W ||^2 + \u955 _curv ||F||_2^2 # bundle curvature (optional)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 conservation loss
\f1\b0 : discrete Noether\
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 invariance loss
\f1\b0 : gauge/group invariance\
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 geometry loss
\f1\b0 : retraction consistency (keeps weights on the manifold)\
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 curvature loss
\f1\b0 : encourages flat, disentangled gauge fibers\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 3) Multi-algebra exchange (safe coercions)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 We allow 
\f0\b coercions
\f1\b0  between algebras with 
\f0\b auditable morphisms
\f1\b0 :\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 (\\mathbb C \\rightarrow \\mathbb H): (a+bi \\mapsto a + bi + 0j + 0k) (complex as quaternions with zero (j,k)).\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 (\\mathbb H \\rightarrow \\mathbb O): 
\f0\b Cayley\'96Dickson
\f1\b0  injection (fix bracketization).\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Projections back are adjoints that 
\f0\b minimize associator error
\f1\b0  (for (\\mathbb O), we keep a fixed left-nesting and monitor ([x,y,z]=(xy)z-x(yz))).\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Clifford
\f1\b0  blocks: via real embeddings; expose blades as channels with antisymmetric multiplication.\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Symmetric-space 
\f12 \uc0\u8596 
\f0  Euclidean
\f1\b0 : retractions (log/exp, QR/Stiefel projection, polar decompositions).\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Every coercion logs a 
\f0\b type witness
\f1\b0  in the ledger:\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 "coercion": \{\
  "from": "H", "to": "O", "rule": "cayley_dickson_left",\
  "associator_norm": 1.3e-4\
\}\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

