	\'95	Hardware variance: Calibration drift is real; always log backend name, date, and mitigation settings, and expect re-runs. Use Heron where possible\'97quality wins over raw qubit count.  \
	\'95	Depth budget: Heavy-hex connectivity penalizes depth with SWAPs. Keep circuits shallow and layout-aware; pre-embed your SU(2) blocks to the coupling map.  \
