\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1) Component IR + Registry (unchanged concept, Ray-aware plumbing)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls272\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 IR (YAML/JSON + dataclass)
\f1\b0 : declares graph of modules (backbone, neck, head, loss, metric) with in_spec
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1 out_spec.\
\ls272\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Registry
\f1\b0 : Python entrypoints resolving strings to modules.\
\ls272\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Ray glue
\f1\b0 : the 
\f0\b TrainerBuilder
\f1\b0  consumes an IR and emits a Ray 
\f0\b TorchTrainer
\f1\b0  with the assembled nn.Module, losses, metrics, and dataloaders backed by 
\f0\b Ray Data
\f1\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Example IR (retinanet50_fpn.yaml)
\f1\b0 :\
model:\
  backbone: backbone/resnet50\
  neck: neck/fpn@fpn_c3_c5\
  head: detector/retina_head@cls_reg(num_classes=80, anchors="retinanet")\
  norm: batchnorm\
  activation: relu\
loss:\
  - loss/focal(gamma=2.0, alpha=0.25, head="cls")\
  - loss/smooth_l1(beta=0.11, head="reg")\
optimizer: adamw(lr=0.0002, betas=[0.9,0.999], weight_decay=0.05)\
lr_schedule: cosine(warmup_steps=1500)\
data:\
  dataset: coco2017\
  transforms: aug/albumentations/coco_retina.yaml\
train:\
  batch_size_per_worker: 16\
  num_epochs: 12\
  precision: amp\
  ddp: fsdp(auto_wrap="resnet_blocks")  # fsdp or deepspeed\
\
