\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 4) Hyperparameter search with Ray Tune\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Use 
\f0\b Tune
\f1\b0  to explore backbones, learning rates, schedulers, and even module choices (e.g., ASPP vs PSPHead), while reusing the same trainer function.\
from ray import tune\
search_space = \{\
  "ir": "configs/retinanet50_fpn.yaml",\
  "lr": tune.loguniform(1e-5, 5e-4),\
  "bs": tune.choice([12, 16]),\
  "amp": True,\
  "epochs": 12\
\}\
tuner = tune.Tuner(\
  trainer,\
  param_space=\{"train_loop_config": search_space\},\
  tune_config=tune.TuneConfig(\
    metric="mAP", mode="max",\
    num_samples=16,\
    scheduler=tune.schedulers.ASHA(max_t=12, grace_period=2)\
  )\
)\
tuner.fit()\
\
