\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 C.3 Task vectors / model merging\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls301\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Compute 
\f0\b \uc0\u916 \u952  = \u952 _finetuned \u8722  \u952 _base
\f1\b0  (task vector).\
\ls301\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Apply 
\f0\b \uc0\u952 _new = \u952 _other + \u945 \'b7\u916 \u952 
\f1\b0  to transfer behavior into another base model.\
\ls301\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Merge with 
\f0\b per-layer scaling & safeguards
\f1\b0  (ignore unmatched keys; clip norms). Works well for vision backbones and LMs (see MergeKit-style recipes).\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 # slate/merge/task_vector.py\
def task_vector(base_sd, tuned_sd):\
    delta = \{\}\
    for k in tuned_sd:\
        if k in base_sd and tuned_sd[k].shape == base_sd[k].shape:\
            delta[k] = tuned_sd[k] - base_sd[k]\
    return delta\
\
def apply_vector(target_sd, delta, alpha=1.0):\
    out = target_sd.copy()\
    for k,v in delta.items():\
        if k in out and out[k].shape == v.shape:\
            out[k] = out[k] + alpha*v\
    return out\
