\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 G) Self-critique & next tightenings\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls304\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 CNN LoRA
\f1\b0  is less standardized than transformer LoRA; our 1\'d71 low-rank adapters on bottleneck projections work well in practice, but we\'92ll also expose 
\f0\b IA\'b3
\f1\b0 -style multiplicative adapters for convs as an option.\
\ls304\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 KD data quality
\f1\b0 : If teacher logits are too peaky, use temperature 
\f0\b T=2\'964
\f1\b0  and increase \uc0\u945  for soft loss (0.8\'960.95).\
\ls304\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Task vectors
\f1\b0 : simple linear merge works best when base models are aligned (identical arch & tokenizer); we include 
\f0\b per-layer scaling
\f1\b0  to reduce regressions.\
\ls304\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 RLHF on LMs
\f1\b0 : for local boxes, prefer 
\f0\b QLoRA
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b 8-bit optimizers
\f1\b0 ; keep sequence length short and use a tiny reward model.\
