\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 3) Regularization alignment (dropout, DropBlock, stochastic depth) + activations\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 We treat regularization as 
\f0\b configurable surfaces
\f1\b0 :\
reg:\
  dropout:\
    head_p: 0.1               # FC/decoder dropout\
    attn_p: 0.0               # transformer attention dropout (keep = pretrained)\
  dropblock:\
    enabled: true\
    block_size: 7\
    p: 0.10                    # per-layer keep prob computed by scheduler\
    targets: ["backbone.layer3", "backbone.layer4"]\
  stochastic_depth:\
    drop_prob: 0.1             # ConvNeXt/ResNet/Vit DropPath\
  label_smoothing: 0.1\
  ema:\
    enabled: false             # true for GAN/diff\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls309\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 CNNs
\f1\b0 : prefer 
\f0\b DropBlock
\f1\b0  (structured) over vanilla dropout in deep conv stacks; apply on late stages where RF is large.\
\ls309\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 ConvNeXt/ResNet
\f1\b0 : 
\f0\b stochastic depth (DropPath)
\f1\b0  with linearly increasing drop rate across depth (0
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1 p).\
\ls309\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Transformers
\f1\b0 : keep 
\f0\b pretrained dropout
\f1\b0 ; for low-data regimes, adjust 
\f0\b head dropout
\f1\b0  only.\
\ls309\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Activations
\f1\b0 : keep 
\f0\b ReLU
\f1\b0  for classic ResNet, 
\f0\b SiLU
\f1\b0  for ConvNeXt/YOLO, 
\f0\b GELU
\f1\b0  for transformers; expose a switch, but changing it may require BN stat reset/warmup.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Scheduler for DropBlock/DropPath
\f1\b0 : warm up from 0 to target p over the first N epochs; you can tune p with Tune.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\partightenfactor0

