\cf0 awesome \'97 here are 
\f0\b ready-to-run Ray Tune grids per batch
\f1\b0 , aligned to the 
\f0\b mathematical operations at each layer
\f1\b0 (conv kernel/stride/dilation/padding, attention heads/QKV dims, norm eps/momentum, residual depth/width, RNN gating, etc.), plus 
\f0\b threading knobs
\f1\b0  (Ray Data/DataLoader concurrency) so you can push the hardware efficiently.\
I keep the code 
\f0\b copy-pasteable
\f1\b0 . Each grid is a 
\f0\b\fs32 param_space
\f1\b0\fs26  dict you can plug into:\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 from ray import tune\
from ray.tune import Tuner, TuneConfig\
from ray.train import RunConfig\
\
tuner = Tuner(\
    my_trainer,                                 # TorchTrainer or RLlib algo\
    param_space=\{ "train_loop_config": GRID \},  # <- pick one GRID below\
    tune_config=TuneConfig(metric="val_metric", mode="max", num_samples=32),\
    run_config=RunConfig(name="study_name")\
)\
tuner.fit()\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

