\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mathematical Appendix (Part 1) \'97 Convolution, Pooling, Residual\
Convolution\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls372\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Output shape
\f1\b0 :\uc0\u8232 H_out = floor((H + 2p \u8722  d(k\u8722 1) \u8722  1)/s + 1).\u8232 Params: k^2 * C_in * C_out + C_out.\u8232 FLOPs: 2 * H_out * W_out * k^2 * C_in * C_out.\
\ls372\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : kernel size, stride, padding, dilation, in/out channels.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Deconvolution\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls373\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Output shape
\f1\b0 :\uc0\u8232 H_out = s(H\u8722 1) \u8722  2p + d(k\u8722 1) + output_pad + 1.\
\ls373\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Risk of checkerboard artifacts 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  prefer interpolate+1\'d71.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Pooling\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls374\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 No params. Same output shape formula as conv.\
\ls374\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Max vs avg tunes invariance.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Residual connections\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls375\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Identity: y = F(x) + x (requires channel/stride match).\
\ls375\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Projection: 1\'d71 conv to align shapes.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Threading
\f1\b0 : for conv-heavy models set torch.threads=1\'962, rely on GPU kernels, tune dl.num_workers.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mathematical Appendix (Part 2) \'97 Attention & RNNs\
Self-Attention\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Inputs: [B,L,d_model].\
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Q,K,V: [B,h,L,d_k], with d_k = d_model/h.\
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Output: [B,L,d_model].\
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Params per layer: \uc0\u8776 4 d_model^2 (Q,K,V,O). FFN \u8776 2 d_model^2 \u945  (\u945 =expansion factor).\
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 FLOPs: O(B h L^2 d_k).\
\ls376\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : d_model, heads, depth, dropout, activation, positional encodings.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 GRU\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls377\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 z = \uc0\u963 (W_z x + U_z h)\
\ls377\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 r = \uc0\u963 (W_r x + U_r h)\
\ls377\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 h~ = tanh(W_h x + U_h (r
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 h))\
\ls377\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 h' = (1\uc0\u8722 z)
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 h + z
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 h~\
\ls377\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : hidden size, layers, dropout, bidirectional flag.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 LSTM\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls378\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 i,f,o gates + candidate c~.\
\ls378\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 c' = f
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 c + i
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 c~, h' = o
\f6 \uc0\u8857 
\f1 tanh(c').\
\ls378\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : hidden size, layers, variational dropout, zoneout.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Threading
\f1\b0 : for RNN-heavy tasks, use shorter rollout.len (RLlib) and TBPTT length control (Ray Train).\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

