\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mathematical Appendix (Part 4) \'97 Multi\uc0\u8209 Scale Fusion (FPN / BiFPN / ASPP / PSP)\
FPN (Feature Pyramid Network)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls395\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Backbone maps
\f1\b0 : C2,C3,C4,C5 with strides s=\{4,8,16,32\} for ResNet\uc0\u8209 style (input H\'d7W).\u8232 P5 = Conv3\'d73(C5); P4 = Conv3\'d73(Conv1\'d71(C4) + upsample(P5)); P3 = Conv3\'d73(Conv1\'d71(C3) + upsample(P4)).\u8232 Optional P6,P7 via stride\u8209 2 conv from P5 for large objects.\
\ls395\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Shapes
\f1\b0 : P_l has H/s_l \'d7 W/s_l with s_l 
\f6 \uc0\u8712 
\f1  \{8,16,32,64,128\} depending on the pyramid level.\
\ls395\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Anchors
\f1\b0 : base size a_l = a0\'b72^(l\uc0\u8722 l0); aspect ratios r
\f6 \uc0\u8712 
\f1 \{0.5,1,2\}.\
\ls395\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : levels \{P3..P5|P6\}, lateral width, smoothing conv (3\'d73), upsample mode.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 BiFPN (EfficientDet)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls396\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Weighted fusion
\f1\b0 : y = \uc0\u931 _i (w_i x_i) / (\u931 _i w_i + \u949 ), with w_i \u8805  0 (learned, relu\u8209 clamped).\
\ls396\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Depthwise separable conv
\f1\b0  after fusion to reduce params/FLOPs.\
\ls396\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Top\uc0\u8209 down & bottom\u8209 up
\f1\b0  fusion repeated R times.\
\ls396\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : repeats R, width, \uc0\u949  for stability.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 ASPP (DeepLab)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls397\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Parallel atrous branches
\f1\b0 : Conv3\'d73 with dilation rates (r1,r2,r3) + image pooling branch; concat then 1\'d71 projection.\
\ls397\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 RF
\f1\b0  grows with dilation; ensure rates fit output_stride (8 or 16).\
\ls397\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : rates (e.g., (6,12,18) or (12,24,36)), projection width, output_stride.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 PSP (Pyramid Pooling)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls398\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Pooling bins
\f1\b0 : pool to fixed grids (1\'d71, 2\'d72, 3\'d73, 6\'d76), upsample to original feat size, concat, 1\'d71 projection.\
\ls398\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Purpose
\f1\b0 : global context injection with low cost.\
\ls398\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Tune knobs
