\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mathematical Appendix (Part 7) \'97 Detection Anchors, Box Parametrization, IoU Losses\
Anchors & Feature Strides\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls408\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 For pyramid level 
\f0\b P_l
\f1\b0  with stride 
\f0\b s_l
\f1\b0  (e.g., 8,16,32,64,128), anchor centers are at pixel grid multiples of 
\f0\b s_l
\f1\b0  in input space.\
\ls408\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Anchor size
\f1\b0 : a_l = a_0 \'b7 2^\{l\uc0\u8722 l_0\}; aspect ratios r
\f6 \uc0\u8712 
\f1 \{0.5,1,2\}. Width/height: w=\uc0\u8730 (a_l^2/r), h=\u8730 (a_l^2\'b7r).\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Box Encoding (t_x, t_y, t_w, t_h)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls409\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Given anchor (x_a,y_a,w_a,h_a) and gt (x,y,w,h):\uc0\u8232 t_x=(x\u8722 x_a)/w_a, t_y=(y\u8722 y_a)/h_a, t_w=log(w/w_a), t_h=log(h/h_a).\
\ls409\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Pred decode: x=x_a + t_x\'b7w_a, y=y_a + t_y\'b7h_a, w=w_a\'b7exp(t_w), h=h_a\'b7exp(t_h).\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 IoU-family Losses\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls410\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 IoU
\f1\b0 : area(intersection)/area(union).\
\ls410\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 GIoU
\f1\b0 : IoU \uc0\u8722  (area(C)\u8722 area(union))/area(C), where C is smallest enclosing box.\
\ls410\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 DIoU
\f1\b0 : IoU \uc0\u8722  (\u961 ^2(b,b_gt)/c^2), center distance penalty.\
\ls410\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 CIoU
\f1\b0 : DIoU \uc0\u8722  \u945 \'b7v, with v measuring aspect ratio consistency, \u945 =v/(1\u8722 IoU+v).\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : anchor base a_0, level set \{P3..P6\}, aspect ratios, IoU variant, focal \uc0\u947 /\u945 ; ensure input size divisible by max stride.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mathematical Appendix (Part 8) \'97 Positional Encodings (Sin/Cos, RoPE, ALiBi)\
Sinusoidal (Vaswani)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls411\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 PE[pos,2i] = sin(pos / 10000^\{2i/d_model\}), PE[pos,2i+1] = cos(pos / 10000^\{2i/d_model\}).\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls412\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Apply rotation to Q,K per head using angle \uc0\u952 (pos):\u8232 RoPE(q_even,q_odd) = (q_even cos\u952  \u8722  q_odd sin\u952 , q_even sin\u952  + q_odd cos\u952 ).\u8232 Same for K; induces relative position in dot\u8209 product.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 ALiBi\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls413\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Add linear bias to attention scores per head:\uc0\u8232 score_\{ij\} 
\f4 \uc0\u8592 
\f1  score_\{ij\} \uc0\u8722  m_h \'b7 |i\u8722 j|.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Tune knobs
\f1\b0 : PE type \{sinusoidal, rope, alibi\}, rope base, head slopes schedule; max_len (8/16 multiples).\
