\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1) Config-first: host-injectable backends & ONNX\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Define a single config schema your host can inject (YAML/env/CLI). Example:\
metrics:\
  flops_backend: fvcore        # fvcore | thop | none\
  log_activations: false       # if true, measure selected activations\
\
export:\
  onnx:\
    enabled: true\
    path: "artifacts/model.onnx"\
    opset: 17\
    dynamic_axes:               # per input / output name\
      input: \{0: "batch", 2: "H", 3:"W"\}   # cv example\
      output: \{0: "batch"\}\
    do_constant_folding: true\
    simplify: true              # run onnxsim if available\
    runtime_check: true         # run an onnxruntime inference sanity check\
    providers: ["CPUExecutionProvider"]  # or CUDAExecutionProvider\
You can pass this config via YAML + OmegaConf, env vars, or Ray Tune (we already merge train_loop_config).\
