\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 4) ONNX-friendly model choices & guardrails\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 To keep exports portable and platform-agnostic, prefer:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Interpolation
\f1\b0 : use mode="nearest" | "bilinear", align_corners=False; these map well to ONNX opset \uc0\u8805  13.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Activations
\f1\b0 : 
\f0\b SiLU
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b GELU
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b ReLU
\f1\b0  are supported in opset \uc0\u8805  14; if targeting older opsets, use approximations (fast-GELU) or switch to ReLU.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 GroupNorm
\f1\b0 /
\f0\b LayerNorm
\f1\b0 : supported; ensure epsilon scalar.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Custom / Python control flow
\f1\b0 : avoid branching/loops inside forward; use Tensor ops only.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 DropPath/DropBlock
\f1\b0 : implement as no-ops at export (eval mode) or wrap under torch.jit.is_scripting()guards.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Concats/Adds
\f1\b0 : keep channel-last concatenations consistent with ONNX shapes.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 RNN
\f1\b0 : prefer nn.GRU/LSTM over scripted cell loops; opset support is better.\
\ls431\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Detection decoders
\f1\b0 : if you keep post-processing (NMS) out of the graph, export only logits/boxes; do NMS in runtime (ONNXRuntime has NMS).\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

