\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 OS Level Services and Service Spec\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f5\i\b0\fs26 \cf0 (Network Atlas \'97 Wiring Optimization & Cell Playbook, Part 2)
\f1\i0 \
This spec defines an 
\f0\b OS-level service
\f1\b0  (daemon atlasd) that exposes a stable 
\f0\b API/RPC/SDK
\f1\b0  for training, tuning, exporting, and serving models with full 
\f0\b traceability
\f1\b0  (math/dim ledger), 
\f0\b portability
\f1\b0  (ONNX), and 
\f0\b policy control
\f1\b0 (throttling & scheduling). It runs identically on a laptop, on edge nodes, or in Kubernetes.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1) Service Overview\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls446\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Process
\f1\b0 : single daemon (systemd service or container) exposing 
\f0\b gRPC
\f1\b0  + 
\f0\b HTTP/JSON
\f1\b0  via grpc-gateway; local 
\f0\b Unix socket
\f1\b0  /var/run/atlas.sock; remote 
\f0\b mTLS TCP
\f1\b0 .\
\ls446\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Backends
\f1\b0 : Ray Data/Train/Tune/Serve; ONNX Runtime for portable inference; FLOPs backends (fvcore/THOP) are 
\f0\b config-injected
\f1\b0 , not hard-coded.\
\ls446\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Artifacts
\f1\b0 : model/onnx/ledger stored in filesystem or object store (S3/MinIO/GCS); registry tracks metadata, metrics, lineage.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

