\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Mentor\'92s Guide (Part 3) \'97 Learning by Rewiring\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 Purpose.
\f1\b0  Make onboarding a 
\f5\i guided apprenticeship
\f1\i0 : every new model is 
\f0\b classified 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  decomposed 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  rewired 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  mentored
\f1\b0  through reproducible studies, observed in Grafana, and promoted with provenance.\

\f0\b How the Guide reads.
\f1\b0  Each chapter uses 
\f5\i context 
\f4\i0 \uc0\u8594 
\f5\i  mechanics 
\f4\i0 \uc0\u8594 
\f5\i  consequence
\f1\i0  (your writing rule) so it \'93teaches why\'94 before \'93what to click.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 A. Cognitive frame (why rewiring works)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls524\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Reflexive hypergraph of knowing
\f1\b0 : treat each model/layer/adapter as a 
\f0\b fiber
\f1\b0  projected from a shared semantic space; rewiring is re-aligning fibers, not bolting parts. We borrow your 
\f0\b Hopf fibration
\f1\b0  metaphor (S\'b9 user frame, S\'b3 semantic total space, S\'b2 projected understanding) to explain why 
\f0\b classification 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  decomposition 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  recomposition
\f1\b0  creates 
\f5\i cognitive resonance
\f1\i0  instead of sprawl.\
\ls524\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Agent-first OS-native nodes
\f1\b0 : emphasize 
\f5\i the user/agent is primary
\f1\i0 ; the platform serves agents, not the other way around. Every rewiring is a small local cognitive act that a node can reason about, try, and promote.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 B. Operational frame (where rewiring runs)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls525\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Corrected execution model
\f1\b0 : rewiring runs 
\f0\b host-first
\f1\b0  when tiny/fast, 
\f0\b LMS K3s
\f1\b0  when it needs isolation/GPU/PII, 
\f0\b edge
\f1\b0  for sensor-adjacent inference, and 
\f0\b fog/cloud
\f1\b0  only when necessary; same contracts everywhere. This section teaches \'93
\f5\i smallest-sufficient tier
\f1\i0 .\'94\
\ls525\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Dual orchestration
\f1\b0 : canonical rewires sit in governed 
\f0\b Airflow
\f1\b0  DAGs; opportunistic fan-out can flow to the 
\f0\b federated mesh
\f1\b0  (WUs in containers/WASM) and reduce back under policy. Students learn when/why to send a rewire to the mesh and how verification modes (redundant/TEE/spot/ZK) establish trust.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 C. Contract frame (how rewiring is recorded and moves)\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls526\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Avro 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  JSON-LD/SALAD 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  TritRPC
