\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1. Cognitive Frame \'97 Why Rewiring Works\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls548\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Ontology:
\f1\b0  Each model, layer, or adapter is a 
\f5\i fiber
\f1\i0  in a reflexive hypergraph; rewiring is aligning fibers, not bolting parts.\
\ls548\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Semantic fibration:
\f1\b0  S\'b9 (agent/user view) projects through S\'b3 (semantic total space) to S\'b2 (model representation). Rewiring keeps the projection consistent with the whole.\
\ls548\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Agent\uc0\u8209 first:
\f1\b0  The user/agent is primary; the OS service plane supports their reasoning and choices.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Mentoring principle:
\f1\b0  Every rewire is a small, legible act of learning; provenance and contracts ensure knowledge accumulates, not fragments.\
