\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 3. Contract Frame \'97 How Rewires Are Recorded\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls550\ilvl0
\f2\b0\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 TritRPC-first:
\f1\b0  All intents, trials, promotions, and serve operations use the 
\f0\b TritRPC
\f1\b0  envelope (TRIT = TRUE/MID/FALSE) as the protocol of record. gRPC/HTTP/Kafka are 
\f0\b transports
\f1\b0  only. The envelope travels unchanged across transports and tiers.\
\ls550\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Avro SALAD + JSON\uc0\u8209 LD:
\f1\b0  Payloads are Avro-typed and semantically pinned via JSON\uc0\u8209 LD contexts. The TritRPC envelope carries code|reason|meta and is mirrored in transport headers (e.g., Kafka x-trit-code).\
\ls550\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Two serialize paths:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls550\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Path A
\f1\b0  
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Avro binary in TritRPC (over HTTP/2 or HTTP/1.1)\
\ls550\ilvl1
\f2\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Path B
\f1\b0  
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Avro\uc0\u8209 T3 ternary encoding (TritPack243) for B3/Q3 channels\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls550\ilvl0
\f2\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 Immutable trail:
\f1\b0  Each trial emits ledger.json, onnx_check.json, model_card.json (+ trace SVG/JSON). Promotion writes a signed, auditable card.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Mentoring principle:
\f1\b0  The 
\f5\i protocol
\f1\i0  is TritRPC; the 
\f5\i plumbing
\f1\i0  can vary. Consistency of the envelope is what guarantees traceability.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

